    "chapter": {
        "bookTitle": "Amos",
        "delineation": "Chapter",
        "number": 5,
        "summary": "The people of Israel are exhorted to seek the Lord and do good so that they may live\u2014Their sacrifices to false gods are abhorrent.",
        "chapterAugmentations": [],
        "verses": [
            {
                "text": "Hear ye this word which I take up against you, even a lamentation, O house of Israel.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 47,
                        "end": 51
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "The virgin of Israel is fallen; she shall no more rise: she is forsaken upon her land; there is none to raise her up.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 87,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For thus saith the Lord God; The city that went out by a thousand shall leave an hundred, and that which went forth by an hundred shall leave ten, to the house of Israel.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 52,
                        "end": 54
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 118
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For thus saith the Lord unto the house of Israel, Seek ye me, and ye shall live:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 1:20; Mosiah 26:30.",
                        "start": 50,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But seek not Beth-el, nor enter into Gilgal, and pass not to Beer-sheba: for Gilgal shall surely go into captivity, and Beth-el shall come to nought.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 3:14.",
                        "start": 120,
                        "end": 127
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Seek the Lord, and ye shall live; lest he break out like fire in the house of Joseph, and devour it, and there be none to quench it in Beth-el.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "1\u00a0Chr. 16:11; Alma 37:47; Ether 12:41; D&C 45:46; 88:63; 101:38.",
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 4
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 100
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 105,
                        "end": 113
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 129,
                        "end": 131
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Ye who turn judgment to wormwood, and leave off righteousness in the earth,",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Seek him that maketh the seven stars and Orion, and turneth the shadow of death into the morning, and maketh the day dark with night: that calleth for the waters of the sea, and poureth them out upon the face of the earth: The Lord is his name:",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0the Pleiades.",
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Astronomy.",
                        "start": 31,
                        "end": 36
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 4:13.",
                        "start": 89,
                        "end": 96
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 8:9.",
                        "start": 117,
                        "end": 121
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 9:6.",
                        "start": 155,
                        "end": 161
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 8
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 232,
                        "end": 234
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "That strengtheneth the spoiled against the strong, so that the spoiled shall come against the fortress.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "They hate him that rebuketh in the gate, and they abhor him that speaketh uprightly.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 27:32.",
                        "start": 35,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Forasmuch therefore as your treading is upon the poor, and ye take from him burdens of wheat: ye have built houses of hewn stone, but ye shall not dwell in them; ye have planted pleasant vineyards, but ye shall not drink wine of them.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Zeph. 1:13.",
                        "start": 102,
                        "end": 107
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Deut. 28:30.",
                        "start": 147,
                        "end": 152
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 37,
                        "end": 39
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "For I know your manifold transgressions and your mighty sins: they afflict the just, they take a bribe, and they turn aside the poor in the gate from their right.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Bribe.",
                        "start": 97,
                        "end": 102
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 29:21.",
                        "start": 113,
                        "end": 117
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ezek. 22:7 (7\u201313); Hel. 6:39 (37\u201340).",
                        "start": 128,
                        "end": 132
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 145,
                        "end": 162
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore the prudent shall keep silence in that time; for it is an evil time.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Prudence.",
                        "start": 14,
                        "end": 21
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Prov. 17:28 (27\u201328).",
                        "start": 33,
                        "end": 40
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 62,
                        "end": 64
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Seek good, and not evil, that ye may live: and so the Lord, the God of hosts, shall be with you, as ye have spoken.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Ether 4:12 (11\u201312); Moro. 7:16; D&C 6:13; 58:28 (26\u201333).",
                        "start": 5,
                        "end": 9
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Evil.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Hate the evil, and love the good, and establish judgment in the gate: it may be that the Lord God of hosts will be gracious unto the remnant of Joseph.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Love.",
                        "start": 19,
                        "end": 23
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "2\u00a0Ne. 3:4; 25:21; Jacob 2:25.",
                        "start": 144,
                        "end": 150
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [
                    {
                        "type": "paper-page-number",
                        "data": 1142
                    }
                ],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore the Lord, the God of hosts, the Lord, saith thus; Wailing shall be in all streets; and they shall say in all the highways, Alas! alas! and they shall call the husbandman to mourning, and such as are skilful of lamentation to wailing.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 68,
                        "end": 76
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "And in all vineyards shall be wailing: for I will pass through thee, saith the Lord.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 21,
                        "end": 29
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Woe unto you that desire the day of the Lord! to what end is it for you? the day of the Lord is darkness, and not light.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 5:19 (18\u201319).",
                        "start": 18,
                        "end": 24
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Joel 1:15; 3\u00a0Ne. 21:20; D&C 45:39 (39\u201342).",
                        "start": 29,
                        "end": 32
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Joel 2:2; D&C 133:49; JS\u2014M 1:33 (32\u201334).",
                        "start": 96,
                        "end": 104
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 58,
                        "end": 60
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 93,
                        "end": 95
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "As if a man did flee from a lion, and a bear met him; or went into the house, and leaned his hand on the wall, and a serpent bit him.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Shall not the day of the Lord be darkness, and not light? even very dark, and no brightness in it?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 0,
                        "end": 5
                    },
                    {
                        "start": 30,
                        "end": 32
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "I hate, I despise your feast days, and I will not smell in your solemn assemblies.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Isa. 1:14.",
                        "start": 23,
                        "end": 28
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "IE\u00a0I will not take heed of your sacrifices, incense, etc.",
                        "start": 39,
                        "end": 40
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Solemn Assembly.",
                        "start": 64,
                        "end": 81
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Though ye offer me burnt offerings and your meat offerings, I will not accept them: neither will I regard the peace offerings of your fat beasts.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Hypocrisy.",
                        "start": 10,
                        "end": 15
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "Hosea 8:13; Mal. 1:10.",
                        "start": 71,
                        "end": 77
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Sacrifice.",
                        "start": 116,
                        "end": 125
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 78,
                        "end": 83
                    }
                ]
            },
            {
                "text": "Take thou away from me the noise of thy songs; for I will not hear the melody of thy viols.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But let judgment run down as waters, and righteousness as a mighty stream.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "Amos 6:12; 2\u00a0Ne. 15:7.",
                        "start": 8,
                        "end": 16
                    },
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Righteousness.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 54
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Have ye offered unto me sacrifices and offerings in the wilderness forty years, O house of Israel?",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "But ye have borne the tabernacle of your Moloch and Chiun your images, the star of your god, which ye made to yourselves.",
                "footnotes": [
                    {
                        "footnote": "TG\u00a0Apostasy of Israel.",
                        "start": 41,
                        "end": 47
                    }
                ],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": []
            },
            {
                "text": "Therefore will I cause you to go into captivity beyond Damascus, saith the Lord, whose name is The God of hosts.",
                "footnotes": [],
                "associatedContents": [],
                "italics": [
                    {
                        "start": 92,
                        "end": 94
                    }
                ]
            }
        ]
    }
}